            <h1 id="whatis">What is Telegram?</h1>
            <p>Telegram is an instant messaging service that is known for their speed and security. It was launched in 2013<br> and has since become the most popular messaging apps, with over 800 million active users.</p>
            <p>Telegram Offer the following servies such as:</p>
            <ol>
              <li><b>End-To-End Encryption</b>: In summary, only you and the recipient can see or read this message!</li>
              <li><b>Linked Devices</b>: It allows you to sync from multiple devices.</li>
              <li><b>Channels</b>: It allows you to create channels and broadcast to a large audience.</li>
              <li><b>Personal Messaging</b>: It allows you to send or receive messages, videos, photos, or files with your friends and family.</li>
            </ol>
            <p>Some requirements before you start, ensure that you have the following requirements!</p>
            <ol>
              <li>A Smartphone</li>
              <li><b>A Valid Phone Number</b> linked to your Smartphone. </li>
              <li>A sufficient mobile phone storage!</li>
              <li>Optional: Laptop & PC Requires you to set up your account previously!</li>
            </ol>
