          <h1 id="FAQ">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
          <button class="collapsible">What is Telegram For?</button>
          <div class="content">
            <p>Telegram is for anyone who wants quick and dependable messaging and calling.<br><br> Large groups, usernames, desktop apps, and powerful file sharing options may appeal to business users and small teams. Because Telegram groups can have up to 200,000 members, we support replies, mentions, and hashtags to help maintain order and communication efficiency in large communities. <br><br> You can empower administrators with advanced tools to help these communities thrive in peace. Anyone can join public groups, which are powerful platforms for discussions and feedback.</p>
          </div>
          <button class="collapsible">Where did Telegram came from?</button>
          <div class="content">
            <p>The development team for Telegram is based in Dubai. <br><br>
              The majority of Telegram's developers are originally from St. Petersburg, a city known for its unprecedented number of highly skilled engineers. <br><br>Due to local IT regulations, the Telegram team was forced to leave Russia and has established bases in Berlin, London, and Singapore. We are currently content in Dubai, but are prepared to relocate if local regulations change.</p>
          </div>
          <button class="collapsible">Thoughts on Internet Privacy</button>
          <div class="content">
            <p>We believe that the two most important aspects of Internet privacy are:</p>
            <ol><li>Protecting your private conversations from prying eyes such as officials, employers, and others.</li><li>Keeping your personal information safe from third parties such as marketers, advertisers, and so on.</li><li>Telegram's goal is to create a truly free messenger with a groundbreaking privacy policy.</li></ol>
          </div>
